<definition-item><classification-symbol scheme="cpc">F28G</classification-symbol><definition-title>CLEANING OF INTERNAL OR EXTERNAL SURFACES OF HEAT-EXCHANGE OR HEAT-TRANSFER CONDUITS, e.g. WATER TUBES OR BOILERS  (cleaning pipes or tubes in general <class-ref scheme="cpc">B08B9/02</class-ref>; devices or arrangements for removing water, minerals, or sludge from boilers while the boiler is in operation, or which remain in position while the boiler is in operation, or are specifically adapted to boilers without any other utility <class-ref scheme="cpc">F22B37/48</class-ref>; removal or treatment of combustion products or combustion residues <class-ref scheme="cpc">F23J</class-ref>; removing ice from heat-exchange apparatus <class-ref scheme="cpc">F28F17/00</class-ref>)</definition-title><definition-statement>
